4 (b) The holder of the security interest shall cause the
5 certificate of title, application and fee and the copy of the
6 application to be mailed or delivered to the department.
7 (c) The department shall indicate on the copy of the
8 application the date and place of filing of the application.
9 (d) Upon On receipt of the certificate of title, application
10 and the required fee, the department shall issue a new certificate
11 in the form provided by section 222 setting forth the name and
12 address of each holder of a security interest in the vehicle or in
13 any accessory on the vehicle for which a termination statement has
14 not been filed and the date on which the application first stating
15 the security interest was filed, and mail the certificate to the
16 owner. However, as provided under this section, the secretary of
17 state is not required to issue a title to the owner of a vehicle if
18 the title is subject to a security interest.
19 (2) A holder of any kind of a security interest may assign,
20 absolutely or otherwise, the holder's security interest in the
21 vehicle or any accessory thereon on the vehicle to a person other
22 than the owner without affecting the interest of the owner or the
23 validity of the security interest, but any person without notice of
24 the assignment is protected in dealing with the holder of the
25 security interest as the holder thereof.of the security interest.
26 (3) If a person rejects the assignment or the purchase of a
27 motor vehicle lease agreement or installment sale contract, or at
28 any time after accepting the assignment or purchase of a motor
29 vehicle lease agreement or installment sale contract, the person
