13 (4) (3) The assignee of a security interest may have the
14 certificate of title indorsed with the assignee named as the holder
15 of the security interest by providing the department with a copy of
16 the assignment instrument, but the failure of the assignee to do so
17 shall does not affect the validity of the security interest of that
18 assignment.
19 (5) (4) If there is no outstanding obligation and no
20 commitment to make advances, incur obligations, or otherwise give
21 value secured or to be secured by a security interest in a vehicle
22 or an accessory on the vehicle, for which the certificate of title
23 is in possession of a secured party, the secured party may, not
24 more than 14 days after satisfaction of the obligation, execute a
25 termination statement in the form prescribed by the department and
26 mail or deliver the termination statement to the owner or another
27 person as the owner may direct.
28 (6) (5) If there is no outstanding obligation and no
29 commitment to make advances, incur obligations, or otherwise give
