1 value secured or to be secured by a security interest in a vehicle
2 or an accessory on the vehicle, for which the certificate of title
3 is in the possession of another person, the secured party shall,
4 within 14 days after demand but not more than 30 days after demand,
5 execute a termination statement in the form prescribed by the
6 department and mail or deliver the termination statement to the
7 owner or another person as the owner may direct.
8 (7) (6) The department may require that all transactions
9 concerning vehicle title liens and security interests be conducted
10 by electronic means, as determined by the department. After all
11 liens have been terminated, or for purposes of retitling the
12 vehicle in another state or any other purpose deemed appropriate by
13 the department, the department may issue a paper copy of the
14 vehicle title to the vehicle's owner.
15 (8) (7) A vehicle sale transaction in which a security
16 interest is entered by electronic means shall must include a
17 document recording entry of the electronic security interest and
18 information regarding the financial institution that holds the
19 security interest. At the time a security interest is presented
20 with payment in satisfaction of the security interest, a secured
21 receipt in a form approved by the department and produced at the
22 time the security interest is presented with payment in
23 satisfaction of the security interest may be submitted to the
24 department in lieu of the title for purposes of transferring
25 ownership in the vehicle.
26 (9) As used in this section, "installment buyer", "installment
27 sale contract", and "installment seller" mean those terms as
28 defined in section 2 of the motor vehicle sales finance act, 1950
