1 Sec. 806. (1) Until October 1, 2027, an applicant for a
2 certificate of title required by this act or an applicant for a
3 duplicate of a certificate of title shall accompany the application
4 with a fee of $10.00. An applicant that requests that the
5 application be given special expeditious treatment shall accompany
6 the application with an additional fee of $5.00. The secretary of
7 state shall collect a $3.00 service fee, in addition to the other
8 fees collected under this subsection, for each title issued and
9 shall deposit the fee in the transportation administration
10 collection fund created under section 810b through October 1, 2027.
11 Until October 1, 2027, the $5.00 expeditious treatment fee must be
12 deposited into the transportation administration collection fund
13 created under section 810b.
14 (2) An applicant for a special identifying number under
15 section 230 shall accompany the application with a fee of $10.00.
16 (3) In addition to paying the fees required by subsection (1),
17 until December 31, 2027, each person that applies for a certificate
18 of title, a salvage vehicle certificate of title, or a scrap
19 certificate of title under this act shall pay a tire disposal
20 surcharge of $1.50 for each certificate of title or duplicate of a
21 certificate of title that person receives. The secretary of state
22 shall deposit money received under this subsection into the scrap
23 tire regulatory fund created in section 16908 of the natural
24 resources and environmental protection act, 1994 PA 451, MCL
25 324.16908.
26 (4) Beginning January 1, 2027 and subject to this subsection,
27 a dealer required to submit an application for title for the sale
28 or lease of a motor vehicle shall submit with each application for
29 title an additional fee of $3.00. The secretary of state shall
