19 (5) The motor vehicle sales finance act fund is created in the
20 state treasury.
21 (6) The state treasurer shall deposit money and other assets
22 received from the fees collected under subsection (4) and the motor
23 vehicle sales finance act, 1950 (Ex Sess) PA 27, MCL 492.101 to
24 492.141, or from any other source in the fund. The state treasurer
25 shall direct the investment of money in the fund and credit
26 interest and earnings from the investments to the fund. Money in
27 the fund at the close of the fiscal year remains in the fund and
28 does not lapse to the general fund.
29 (7) The department of insurance and financial services is the
